Award-winning Nigerian gospel singer, Sinach, has reacted to the death of Osinachi Nwachukwu. The ‘Ekwueme’ singer died at an Abuja hospital on Friday. Osinachi’s sister confirmed that the talented singer died as a result of a cluster of blood in the chest from the kicking she got from her husband, Mr Peter Nwachukwu. Frank Edwards, Chioma Jesus, Dunsin Oyekan and other gospel artistes have expressed their displeasure about the circumstances surrounding their colleague’s death. Reacting in a post on her Instagram page, Sinach put up a short note wherein she described Osinachi Nwachukwu as a “good soldier”. She prayed for the children and family of the deceased. “Praying for your children and family. Rest well, good soldier,” Sinach wrote. Meanwhile, Daughter of Pastor Paul Enenche of Dunamis International Gospel Center, Deborah, has revealed that the pastor was not aware Osinachi was being abused by her husband. Enenche assured that justice will be served and the children will be protected.